	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=142757"><span id="Scholar">Dread Lord Elenrak</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">18 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.55]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Here's the proof, in my opinion.<br/><br/><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1>Chromospheric<br/>1: Decrease Spell Mana Cost by 25%<br/><b>2: Limit: Spell(Sun Vortex allowed)</b><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE><br/><br/>Note the Sun Vortex allowed.&nbsp;&nbsp;This doesn't mean all spells including Sun Vortex work, otherwise they would have just omitted the limit remark.  This means Sun Vortex ONLY is affected.<br/><br/>Another example is Anger of E'ci.  Since E'ci is the god of ice, essentially, the focus including its name makes sense:<br/><br/><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1>1: Increase Spell Damage by 23%<br/>2: Limit: Max Level(65)<br/>3: Limit: Effect(Hitpoints allowed)<br/>4: Limit: Instant spells only<br/>5: Limit: Spell Type(Detrimental only)<br/>6: Limit: Target(AE PC v1 excluded)<br/>7: Limit: Target(PB AE excluded)<br/>8: Limit: Target(Targeted AE excluded)<br/>9: Limit: Target(Uber Giants excluded)<br/>10: Limit: Target(Uber Dragons excluded)<br/><b>11: Limit: Resist(Cold allowed)</b><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE><br/><br/>The line that &quot;allows&quot; something, basically means that only that type of spell will work.  Casting a nuke that checks resist against Magic will not work with E'ci focus. Only spells that check resist against cold, such as the cold based druid nuke, will be affected.<br/><br/>So the same goes for sanguine Preservation.  Since the only &quot;allowed&quot; spells are Self, the spells that the focus affects, are ones that are tagged as Self.<br/><BLOCKQUOTE><b id=fs8>Quote:</b><hr size=1>1: Decrease Spell Mana Cost by 40% <br/>2: Limit: Max Level(65) <br/>3: Limit: Spell(Complete Healing excluded) <br/>4: Limit: Spell Type(Beneficial only) <br/><b>5: Limit: Target(Self allowed) </b><br/>6: Limit: Min Duration(6.00 sec) <br/>7: Limit: Effect(Percentage Heal excluded) <br/><hr size=1></BLOCKQUOTE><br/><br/>Following the same guidelines means ONLY self-only spells, that are beneficial, and have a duration will be affected.  I'm willing to bet the Shaman line of Rage spells, or the ranger line of ATK buffs, like Firefist would be affected.  But a regular buff like the shaman Focus would not.<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu May 15 21:56:49 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Elentar Edrahil, 70 Bard<br/>Elenrak Gorthaur, 65 Shaman<br/>Legend of Marr Guild<br/>Rathe Server</td></tr>
